==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commorant
<hw>Com"mo*rant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>commorans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>commorari</ets> to abide;
<ets>com-</ets> + <ets>morari</ets> to delay.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Ordinarily residing; inhabiting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All freeholders within the precinct . . . and all persons
<qex>commorant</qex> therein.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Am. Law)</fld> <def>Inhabiting or occupying
temporarily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commorant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Commorant
<hw>Com"mo*rant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A resident.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hacket.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commoration</ent>⟦br⟧
